This is the notebook where I keep my to-do list, like the one you can see in the picture in [Book Review: Do It Tomorrow](http://www.mostlymaths.net/2010/12/book-review-do-it-tomorrow.html). A quick and cheap way to have a small multi-page notebook you can keep always with you. Of course, calling this origami is a small lie, as you have to use scissors.  

  
I read a very good post about going the analog way ([How analog rituals can amp your productivity](http://the99percent.com/tips/6915/How-Analog-Rituals-Can-Amp-Your-Productivity)) and this was my tool. I could have gone the Moleskine way (I have a pair of 7 odd cm sized pocket notebooks), but this is way cheaper and more handy. When you need one, you only need a A4, it can even have a side written up!  
  
Also, when you finish your notebook, you can unfold it and fold it reversed to have another use!  
  

[![](http://3.bp.blogspot.com/_f3d3llNlZKQ/TSjT0EuA0-I/AAAAAAAACzU/WVBi1wYdrKE/s400/14FinishNotebook.JPG)](http://3.bp.blogspot.com/_f3d3llNlZKQ/TSjT0EuA0-I/AAAAAAAACzU/WVBi1wYdrKE/s1600/14FinishNotebook.JPG)  
This is the finished result  

  
You will need an A4 (or any other size) paper and scissors.

  

[![](http://4.bp.blogspot.com/_f3d3llNlZKQ/TSjLzKSJvBI/AAAAAAAACxc/C_xPaRgFDYM/s400/01Start.JPG)](http://4.bp.blogspot.com/_f3d3llNlZKQ/TSjLzKSJvBI/AAAAAAAACxc/C_xPaRgFDYM/s1600/01Start.JPG)

Put your sheet of paper in a flat surface

[![](http://1.bp.blogspot.com/_f3d3llNlZKQ/TSjL0HqWEoI/AAAAAAAACx8/mtloBJKozx8/s400/05MarkCreases3.JPG)](http://1.bp.blogspot.com/_f3d3llNlZKQ/TSjL0HqWEoI/AAAAAAAACx8/mtloBJKozx8/s1600/05MarkCreases3.JPG)

Fold in half

[![](http://3.bp.blogspot.com/_f3d3llNlZKQ/TSjQ31XhSvI/AAAAAAAACyU/tGcHFyIFT_Y/s400/06MarkCreases4.JPG)](http://3.bp.blogspot.com/_f3d3llNlZKQ/TSjQ31XhSvI/AAAAAAAACyU/tGcHFyIFT_Y/s1600/06MarkCreases4.JPG)

Fold along the sides in quarters

[![](http://3.bp.blogspot.com/_f3d3llNlZKQ/TSjQGCkIcAI/AAAAAAAACyE/GocYKrrmBS0/s400/02FoldHalf2.JPG)](http://3.bp.blogspot.com/_f3d3llNlZKQ/TSjQGCkIcAI/AAAAAAAACyE/GocYKrrmBS0/s1600/02FoldHalf2.JPG)

Unfold and fold in half

[![](http://4.bp.blogspot.com/_f3d3llNlZKQ/TSjQGEDhQjI/AAAAAAAACyM/Fhx_uwcn47A/s400/03MarkCreases1.JPG)](http://4.bp.blogspot.com/_f3d3llNlZKQ/TSjQGEDhQjI/AAAAAAAACyM/Fhx_uwcn47A/s1600/03MarkCreases1.JPG)

And fold along the sides in quarters

[![](http://3.bp.blogspot.com/_f3d3llNlZKQ/TSjQ4GdQTOI/AAAAAAAACyc/QrmHob8iyhk/s400/07FoldAlong.JPG)](http://3.bp.blogspot.com/_f3d3llNlZKQ/TSjQ4GdQTOI/AAAAAAAACyc/QrmHob8iyhk/s1600/07FoldAlong.JPG)

Pinch along the longer crease

[![](http://4.bp.blogspot.com/_f3d3llNlZKQ/TSjQ4TEI5EI/AAAAAAAACyk/Q72zXzJyik4/s400/08CutInner1.JPG)](http://4.bp.blogspot.com/_f3d3llNlZKQ/TSjQ4TEI5EI/AAAAAAAACyk/Q72zXzJyik4/s1600/08CutInner1.JPG)

Cut here...

[![](http://2.bp.blogspot.com/_f3d3llNlZKQ/TSjQ4cDaKzI/AAAAAAAACys/gRM9J5yAKMc/s400/09CutInner2.JPG)](http://2.bp.blogspot.com/_f3d3llNlZKQ/TSjQ4cDaKzI/AAAAAAAACys/gRM9J5yAKMc/s1600/09CutInner2.JPG)

... and here ...

[![](http://1.bp.blogspot.com/_f3d3llNlZKQ/TSjQ4lgQEKI/AAAAAAAACy0/V06b693cxKA/s400/10CutSides1.JPG)](http://1.bp.blogspot.com/_f3d3llNlZKQ/TSjQ4lgQEKI/AAAAAAAACy0/V06b693cxKA/s1600/10CutSides1.JPG)

... and here. Cut also in the same spot above.

[![](http://4.bp.blogspot.com/_f3d3llNlZKQ/TSnAyH_wtaI/AAAAAAAACzg/WLHSXdrXEuE/s400/SpineUp.JPG)](http://4.bp.blogspot.com/_f3d3llNlZKQ/TSnAyH_wtaI/AAAAAAAACzg/WLHSXdrXEuE/s1600/SpineUp.JPG)

It will look like this  

[![](http://2.bp.blogspot.com/_f3d3llNlZKQ/TSnAydvx0qI/AAAAAAAACzo/i7wOGe3Wbqc/s400/Pinching.JPG)](http://2.bp.blogspot.com/_f3d3llNlZKQ/TSnAydvx0qI/AAAAAAAACzo/i7wOGe3Wbqc/s1600/Pinching.JPG)

Pinch both sides, folding the sides to the center, from below.  

[![](http://1.bp.blogspot.com/_f3d3llNlZKQ/TSnAzOwJKTI/AAAAAAAAC0A/yaZUumPdqdw/s400/Flattening1.JPG)](http://1.bp.blogspot.com/_f3d3llNlZKQ/TSnAzOwJKTI/AAAAAAAAC0A/yaZUumPdqdw/s1600/Flattening1.JPG)

Finish the folding and hold.  

[![](http://2.bp.blogspot.com/_f3d3llNlZKQ/TSnAy8gbL8I/AAAAAAAACz4/cxo2it4qnQI/s400/Flattening2.JPG)](http://2.bp.blogspot.com/_f3d3llNlZKQ/TSnAy8gbL8I/AAAAAAAACz4/cxo2it4qnQI/s1600/Flattening2.JPG)

Flatten all flaps to the part below. The top area should hold the less paper folds.  

[![](http://2.bp.blogspot.com/_f3d3llNlZKQ/TSnAyjIIS7I/AAAAAAAACzw/uaOfZUIPV7U/s400/FoldInHalf.JPG)](http://2.bp.blogspot.com/_f3d3llNlZKQ/TSnAyjIIS7I/AAAAAAAACzw/uaOfZUIPV7U/s1600/FoldInHalf.JPG)

Fold sideways.  

[![](http://4.bp.blogspot.com/_f3d3llNlZKQ/TSnA2xXZNoI/AAAAAAAAC0I/Yp-LL8MjFSY/s400/Flatten.JPG)](http://4.bp.blogspot.com/_f3d3llNlZKQ/TSnA2xXZNoI/AAAAAAAAC0I/Yp-LL8MjFSY/s1600/Flatten.JPG)

Fold top to bottom.  

[![](http://3.bp.blogspot.com/_f3d3llNlZKQ/TSjT0EuA0-I/AAAAAAAACzU/WVBi1wYdrKE/s400/14FinishNotebook.JPG)](http://3.bp.blogspot.com/_f3d3llNlZKQ/TSjT0EuA0-I/AAAAAAAACzU/WVBi1wYdrKE/s1600/14FinishNotebook.JPG)

Flatten strongly. Ready to use!

